as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."]},{"name":"Mared","meanings":["Simplified form of   Marged ."]}]},{"name":"ferch","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["German: variant of   Ferg  . Compare   Verch  .","Probably also an Americanized form of German <b>Förtsch</b> (see   Foertsch  ).","Probably also an Americanized form of German <b>Förch</b> (see   Foerch  )."],"variants":[{"name":"Ferg","meanings":["1  ‘Sharp blade’.","2  ‘Wind’."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Margred ferch Maredudd was born about 1320, in Hope, Flintshire, Wales, United Kingdom, her father, Maredudd Y Goch ap Ieuan, was 34 and her mother, Efa ferch Cynwrig, was 37. She married Iorwerth Foel ap Iorwerth about 1415, in Denbighshire, Wales, United Kingdom."},"et":{"about 1320–":"umbes 1320–Surnud","1305–Male":"1305–Surnud","1308–Male":"1308–Surnud","1315–Male":"1315–Surnud","1320–Female":"1320–Surnud","1330–Female":"1330–Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1288–Male":"1288–Surnud","1285–Female":"1285–Surnud","1305":"1305","1315":"1315","Abt 1332":"umbes 1332","1288":"1288","1320":"1320","1330":"1330","1285":"1285","about 1320":"umbes 1320","1308":"1308","Abt 1415":"umbes 1415","Plas Maen, Hope, Flintshire, Wales":"Hope, Flintshire, Wales, United Kingdom","OF, PLAS MAEN, HOPE, DENBIGH, WALES":"Denbighshire, Wales, United Kingdom","Plas Maen, Hope, Denbigh, Wales":"Hope, Montgomeryshire, Wales, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1320–":"noin 1320–Kuollut","1305–Ma